body:
Due to React Native's lack of `URL` (see #6142), a simple import of `URL` and `instanceof` check against it won't work as in #5771.

There exist URL polyfills such as [whatwg-url](https://github.com/jsdom/whatwg-url) and [react-native-url-polyfill](https://github.com/charpeni/react-native-url-polyfill), but these are heavy-weight and over-kill.

Ultimately, the fix doesn't need to do anything crazy with `URL`. It only needs to know not to treat it as a simple enumerable object, and cast the value to a string for serialization and equality comparison.

The na√Øve way would be to check the `.constructor.name` property of the value and check for `"URL"`, but this doesn't consider subclassing or other objects called URL.

However, since native `URL` exists in Node (globally since v10.0.0, via import since v6.13.0), and in modern browsers, perhaps a simpler test can be employed as a method on `OrmUtils`, where imports aren't required, and execution won't throw where `URL` doesn't exist.

```ts
isInstanceOfGlobalURL(item: any): boolean {
    // safe way of checking for global URL
    const GlobalURL = typeof URL === "function" ? URL : null;

    if (GlobalURL === null) {
        return false;
    }

    return item instanceof GlobalURL;
}
```

@pleerock, how does this sound?
